article.description: Josh Williams had 14 points and six rebounds as Robert Morris beat Wagner 69-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Williams scores 14 to lift Robert Morris over Wagner 69-60
article.linkText: Williams scores 14 to lift Robert Morris over Wagner 69-60
article.story: NEW YORK -- Josh Williams had 14 points and six rebounds as Robert Morris beat Wagner 69-60 on Saturday. Jon Williams had 12 points and eight assists for Robert Morris (16-15, 11-7 Northeast Conference), which snapped its four-game road losing streak. Yannis Mendy added 10 points. Charles Bain had 10 points for the visiting team. Romone Saunders had 26 points and nine rebounds for the Seahawks (13-16, 8-10), whose losing streak reached four games. Elijah Davis added 17 points. The Colonials improved to 2-0 against the Seahawks on the season. Robert Morris defeated Wagner 57-51 on Jan. 26. The Colonials and the Seahawks next take the floor in the Northeast Conference Tournament. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
